<p>Aldrich Ames, a former CIA counterintelligence officer convicted of spying for the Soviet Union and later Russia, has died in federal custody at age 84, US officials said. The Bureau of Prisons confirmed he died on Monday in a Maryland prison. Ames had been serving a life sentence without parole after pleading guilty in 1994 to espionage and tax evasion, following his February 1994 arrest alongside his wife, Rosario, who was convicted of aiding and abetting.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/6lHIu56VTY13-JPiR42uS0Zt_ytNj14blHzMloYlFLOwCWc6qCWMWmQT6nTxcNk1wfyGlfZUmTpQrI8CZYxu93YW1l4UrNMNUPj7NEc9h1EGLrfi5n5hCRLUe_5sNZHHTwT3P8yaioVuFtgux3uJTZgQuZzEGc37CZwRADBvbRIZgddcUo7z2CZtVNjyvhJszxQ6mgHs2SJ7CQH5LSERxLCPW3UF7TUcd7V7XOkpr8AwV9b-THGdgcIObw' alt='Aldrich Ames pleaded guilty without a trial to espionage and tax evasion and was sentenced to life in prison without parole.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Damage assessment: The BBC reports Ames compromised more than 100 operations and betrayed more than 30 agents who were spying for the West.</li><li>Role at CIA: Ames led the Soviet branch within the CIA’s counterintelligence group, giving the Kremlin the names of dozens of Russians who were spying for the United States.</li><li>Length of spying: He admitted to passing information to Moscow for nearly a decade, in what outlets describe as among the most damaging US intelligence breaches.</li><li>Case closure: He pleaded guilty without a trial, and his wife Rosario was charged in connection with the espionage case, bringing a definitive legal end to a long-running counterintelligence hunt.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>US Bureau of Prisons: The Bureau of Prisons confirmed Ames’ death in custody on Monday in Maryland, according to reporting that cited the agency’s confirmation. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2026/jan/06/aldrich-ames-cia-agent-dead'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Media assessments of impact: Multiple outlets frame Ames’ actions as exceptionally damaging to Western intelligence, emphasizing the breadth of operations and agents he compromised. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cj0n29395j3o'>BBC News</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://en.mercopress.com/2026/01/07/convicted-cia-mole-serving-life-with-no-parole-dies-in-jail'>Convicted CIA mole serving life with no parole dies in jail</a> - mercopress.com</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/2026/01/07/ex-cia-agent-aldrich-ames-convicted-of-spying-for-soviet-union-dies-in-prison-us-officials'>Ex-CIA agent Aldrich Ames convicted of spying for Soviet Union dies in prison, US officials say</a> - euronews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2026-01-07/cia-turncoat-aldrich-ames-who-sold-us-secrets-to-the-soviets-die/106207464'>Ex-CIA agent convicted of spying for Soviets dies in prison</a> - abc.net.au</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/cia-turncoat-aldrich-ames-who-sold-us-secrets-to-the-soviets-dies-in-prison-at-84'>CIA turncoat Aldrich Ames, who sold U.S. secrets to Soviets, dies in prison at 84</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/united-states/cia-turncoat-aldrich-ames-who-helped-the-soviets-dies-at-84'>CIA turncoat Aldrich Ames, who helped the Soviets, dies at 84</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2026/jan/06/aldrich-ames-cia-agent-dead'>Aldrich Ames, CIA agent who spied for Soviet Union and Russia, dies aged 84</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cj0n29395j3o'>Aldrich Ames, CIA agent who sold secrets to the Soviets, dies aged 84</a> - bbc.com</li></ul>